cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on sentence-level sentiment classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel deep neural network model, which involves training two convolutional neural networks, indicating that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Additionally, the model involves a noise transition layer, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as noise reduction is a common problem in image processing. The paper also involves training the two networks in a mutual reinforcement manner, which could indicate that it falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves classification, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
